Reserve first 32 MiB for NXP LS1046A firmware boundary.

Shift BIOS boot and EFI partitions past the 32 MiB NXP firmware zone.
Update CONST_RESERVED_SPACE to match (32 + 1 + 256 MiB).
Use sgdisk end-sector 0 (fill remaining space) when user chooses
"use all free space" to avoid double-counting reserved space.

On eMMC (mmcblk) devices, replace destructive sgdisk -Z with sgdisk -o
(create fresh empty GPT) that only writes minimal headers without bulk
zeroing, and skip wipefs on the raw device to avoid scanning the
firmware zone for filesystem signatures.

diff --git a/python/vyos/system/disk.py b/python/vyos/system/disk.py
index 7ae9a15..dd7ed39 100644
--- a/python/vyos/system/disk.py
+++ b/python/vyos/system/disk.py
@@ -42,6 +42,17 @@ def disk_cleanup(drive_path: str) -> None:
     partitions: list[str] = partition_list(drive_path)
     for partition in partitions:
         run(f'wipefs -af {partition}')
+
+    # On eMMC (mmcblk) devices, preserve the first 32 MiB firmware zone.
+    # NXP LS1046A reserves 0-32 MiB for firmware boundary on eMMC.
+    # sgdisk -Z zeroes GPT/MBR headers and wipefs -af scans for signatures
+    # that may exist within the firmware zone. Use sgdisk -o to create a
+    # fresh empty GPT (writes only protective MBR + header + empty entries
+    # at sectors 0-33 and backup GPT at end, no bulk zeroing).
+    if 'mmcblk' in drive_path:
+        run(f'sgdisk -o {drive_path}')
+        return
+
     run(f'wipefs -af {drive_path}')
     run(f'sgdisk -Z {drive_path}')
 
